# API Endpoints

## Authentication

| Method | Endpoint           | Description   |
| ------ | ------------------ | ------------- |
| POST   | /api/auth/register | Register user |
| POST   | /api/auth/login    | Login user    |
| POST   | /api/auth/logout   | Logout user   |

## Trips

| Method | Endpoint           | Description      |
| ------ | ------------------ | ---------------- |
| POST   | /api/trips/upload  | Upload trip CSV  |
| GET    | /api/trips         | Get user trips   |
| GET    | /api/trips/:tripId | Get trip details |
| DELETE | /api/trips/:tripId | Delete trip      |


---
# How It Works

## 1. CSV Upload

Users upload a GPS trip CSV file containing:

- Latitude
- Longitude
- Timestamp
- Ignition status

The backend processes the CSV file and extracts trip telemetry data.

---

## 2. Distance Calculation

The system calculates total trip distance using the Haversine Formula between GPS coordinates.

---

## 3. Speed Calculation

Speed is calculated using:

- Distance travelled
- Time difference between GPS points

Overspeed is detected when speed exceeds the defined threshold.

---

## 4. Idle & Stoppage Detection

### Idle
Detected when:
- Speed = 0
- Ignition = ON

### Stoppage
Detected when:
- Speed = 0
- Ignition = OFF

---

## 5. Trip Segmentation

Trips are automatically divided into smaller segments for:

- Better analytics
- Easier route inspection
- Segment-based filtering

---

## 6. Interactive Map Rendering

The frontend visualizes:

- Full route
- Overspeed sections
- Idle points
- Stoppage points

Users can switch between segments, and the map dynamically zooms to the selected route.

---

## 7. Analytics Dashboard

The dashboard displays:

- Total distance
- Total duration
- Idle duration
- Stoppage duration
- Overspeed duration

along with paginated telemetry data.
